Tracking Timeliness of Auckland Buses Trips from the Shore to Auckland University

Image of time


The data was collect by five students that travel to uni daily by bus. The information was tracked through observational logging by completing a Google form survey. To maintain accuracy in the data collection process all on-boarding bus times were checked when the individual tagged on through their AT HOP card, and the timeliness of the bus was measured of weather the bus arrived on scheduled time based off the AT HOP Mobile app or not.

We are analysing if a bus is arriving on their scheduled time at the bus stop at different regions from the North shore or not and if they are not then how late are they arriving. We would also like to find out which particular buses are the most late, and weather there is a certain time that most buses are arriving late. The survey was only given to students who live on the North Shore suburbs, which is define as any place between North of the Auckland Harbour Bridge and Albany. Furthermore, the bus lateness was only recorded for the first bus they caught on their trip (if they had caught more than one bus to reach their destination).
